					<div class="post">
				<h3>Re: So far...</h3>
				<div class="date">Posted: <strong>Mon Jun 08, 2020 6:16 pm</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>SteveC</strong></div>
				<div class="content">Oh BTW a few days ago I got the e-paper fully stuck down without a single artifact  <img class="smilies" src="./images/smilies/icon_e_biggrin.gif" width="15" height="17" alt=":D" title="Very Happy"> <br>
<br>
I noticed you could slowly decrease the bend radius over a few days but as soon as the curve was released to apply 3M double sided tape, the previous curving was was lost. It seems the e-paper can reset its curve memory in seconds.<br>
<br>
What worked for me; position the 3M double-sided tape and remove the backing, slowly decrease the e-paper bend radius over several days (as per Justine's video), keep going until all the tape is in contact with the e-paper - done!</div>
			</div>
			<hr />
					<div class="post">
				<h3>Re: So far...</h3>
				<div class="date">Posted: <strong>Wed Jun 10, 2020 5:51 pm</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>nemomtt</strong></div>
				<div class="content">SteveC,<br>
For the lettering, I modified the STL model and added the negative indentation for the lettering using a boolean difference method. After printing I sprayed a small amount of flat black paint into a cup and used a small syringe to insert the paint in the indentations.  After the paint is dry I carefully removed any excess paint with a small amount of brake cleaner and or light sanding.  I printed the case with SpiderMaker 3D Premium Matte PLA+ Filament.  This PLA is very good for reworking.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your insight on laying down the e-paper display.  To tell the truth I have had very poor luck with the e-paper displays.  It is a shame because the bistatic technology is very cool. I have tried to be very careful while installing to e-paper, however, my failure rate is very high. In fact, the one you see on the phone was my third attempt, and that one failed five days after it was installed. I am waiting till I have serval on hand before open the case and try again.  I have some coming in from China as no distributor in the US has any in stock.  I am assuming that the failure rate has something to do with this shortage. I am hoping that Justine comes up with something a little more stable for her next design as she is a brilliant engineer and this seems to be the only hardware issue with this design.</div>
